b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe30076.htm)  [Next](sbe30078.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0543983862/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n_The Grihya Sutras, Part 2 (SBE30)_ , by Hermann Oldenberg, [1892], at sacred-\ntexts.com\n\n* * *\n\n### PA _T_ ALA 1, SECTION 5.\n\n1\\. Then (follows) in the sixth month the Annapra _s_ ana (i.e. the first\nfeeding with solid food).\n\n2\\. In the fortnight of the increasing moon, under an auspicious\nconstellation, he puts wood on the fire, performs the rites down to the Vyah\n_ri_ ti oblations, and sacrifices (with the Mantras), 'This, O Varu _n_ a'\n(&c.; see I, chap. 27, Sutra 2, down to): 'Hail! Good luck!' Then he gives (to\nthe child) threefold food to eat, curds, honey, and ghee, with (the formula),\n'Bhu _h_ I lay into thee! Bhuva _h_ I lay into thee! Suva _h_ I lay into\nthee!'\n\n3\\. Then he gives him (other) food to eat with (the formula), 'I give thee to\neat the essence of water and of the plants. May water and plants be kind\ntowards thee. May water and plants do no harm to thee.'\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: II, 1, 6](sbe30078.htm)\n\n"